# Project Requirements Document (PRD)

## 1. Project Overview

IdeaConnect is a web platform for entrepreneurs to discover startup ideas, express interest in them, and team up with like-minded individuals to build real ventures. Every day, the system automatically syncs fresh ideas from IdeaBrowser.com, presents them in an easy-to-browse feed, and lets users “raise a hand” on ideas they find exciting. Once enough people have shown interest in the same idea, they can spin up a dedicated team space to collaborate.

This platform exists because great ideas often sit idle for lack of collaborators. By centralizing idea discovery, interest signaling, and team formation, IdeaConnect reduces friction and speeds up the process from inspiration to action. Key objectives for launch are:\
• Smooth, reliable daily idea sync (no duplicates)\
• Intuitive “raise hand” and interest tracking\
• Basic discussion threads around each idea\
• A lightweight team-creation wizard and workspace\
Success will be measured by daily active users, number of interests raised, teams formed, and system uptime.

## 2. In-Scope vs. Out-of-Scope

### In-Scope (v1.0)

*   Automated daily synchronization of ideas from IdeaBrowser.com (via API or scraping)
*   Deduplication and metadata storage (category, difficulty, market size)
*   User authentication (email/password) and profile management
*   Idea browsing, detail pages, “Today’s Idea” highlight
*   One-click “Raise Hand” interest mechanism
*   Listing of interested users per idea
*   Threaded discussion pages with rich-text editor
*   Team formation wizard once an idea hits a configurable interest threshold (e.g., 3 users)
*   Basic team workspace (shared chat channel or message board)
*   Email notifications: signup confirmation, weekly digest, team invitations
*   Admin dashboard for sync status, logs, and manual re-sync

### Out-of-Scope (Phase 1)

*   Advanced AI-driven matching or skills-based teammate suggestions
*   Public team showcase with external visibility
*   Full task management or document-editing in team workspace
*   Mobile-native apps (iOS/Android)
*   Third-party integrations beyond IdeaBrowser.com
*   Fine-grained analytics dashboards
*   Multi-language support

## 3. User Flow

When a new user arrives, they see a landing page with “Today’s Idea,” a brief description, and a prominent signup form. They register with email and password, receive a verification link, and once confirmed, land on the dashboard. The left sidebar shows navigation links: Home (idea feed), My Interests, My Teams, Discussions, and Profile. The main area lists today’s featured idea at top, followed by a paginated feed of recent and related ideas.

To explore, the user clicks an idea card, sees full details (description, metadata, interest count, discussion preview), and taps “Raise Hand” to join. Immediately, they see who else is interested. As more people raise hands, a “Form Team” button lights up. Clicking it launches a simple wizard: name your team, assign roles (optional), and invite others. After creation, the user enters a team workspace—essentially a dedicated discussion thread—where they can talk through next steps. Meanwhile, email notifications keep them in the loop on new interests, invites, and weekly newsletters.

## 4. Core Features

*   **Authentication & Profiles**\
    • Sign up / login / email verification\
    • Profile page with interests, skills, privacy controls
*   **Idea Synchronization**\
    • Daily fetch from IdeaBrowser.com\
    • Deduplication and metadata capture\
    • Admin dashboard for monitoring and manual triggers
*   **Idea Discovery & Detail**\
    • Homepage feed with “Today’s Idea” spotlight\
    • Filtering, pagination, and related-idea suggestions\
    • Idea detail view with metadata and interest stats
*   **Interest Signaling**\
    • One-click “Raise Hand” button\
    • Visual indicator (counter/progress bar)\
    • List of interested users (with privacy settings)\
