*   **Discussion Spaces**\
    • Dedicated thread per idea\
    • Rich-text editor (formatting, links, media embeds)\
    • Nested comments and real-time updates\
    • Mention/tag users and basic moderation tools
*   **Team Formation Wizard**\
    • Trigger once interest threshold met\
    • Define team name, roles, objectives\
    • Invite internal / external participants\
    • Lightweight team workspace for chat
*   **Notifications & Emails**\
    • Welcome and verification emails\
    • Weekly digest of new ideas and trending discussions\
    • Team invitations and match alerts\
    • Unsubscribe / preference management
*   **Admin Dashboard**\
    • Monitor sync jobs, view logs, trigger manual jobs\
    • Manage flagged discussions or users

## 5. Tech Stack & Tools

*   **Frontend:** Next.js 13+ (App Router) with React, TypeScript
*   **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
*   **Backend:** Next.js API routes, Node.js, TypeScript
*   **Database & ORM:** Supabase PostgreSQL + Prisma
*   **Authentication:** Supabase Auth (email/password, webhooks)
*   **UI Components:** Shadcn/UI, Lucide React icons
*   **Forms & Validation:** React Hook Form + Zod
*   **Email Service:** Resend or Nodemailer for transactional emails
*   **Scheduler:** Vercel Cron (for daily sync & digests)
*   **Hosting:** Vercel (with domain `ideaconnect.co`)
*   **IDE & AI Assistants:** Cursor (in-IDE suggestions), Claude Code (terminal code assistance)

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

*   **Performance:**\
    • API responses <200 ms under normal load\
    • Page load <2 s on 4G networks
*   **Scalability:**\
    • Handle up to 10,000 users and 100,000 idea records initially
*   **Security:**\
    • OWASP Top 10 compliance (XSS, SQL Injection prevention)\
    • HTTPS enforced, data encryption at rest & in transit\
    • Proper authentication checks on API routes
*   **Usability & Accessibility:**\
    • WCAG 2.1 AA compliance\
    • Responsive design across desktop and tablet
*   **Reliability & Uptime:**\
    • 99.9% uptime SLA\
    • Automated alerts on sync failures or high error rates
*   **Compliance:**\
    • GDPR-compatible privacy controls\
    • Clear cookie and data policies

## 7. Constraints & Assumptions

*   **IdeaBrowser Integration:**\
    • We assume either a stable public API or permission to scrape HTML.\
    • Scheduling environment supports daily cron jobs.
*   **Supabase:**\
    • Supabase Auth and database are available and performant.
*   **Team Threshold:**\
    • Default “raise hand” threshold is three users, configurable by admin.
*   **User Base:**\
    • Users will access via modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari).
*   **Data Volumes:**\
    • Initial dataset is moderate; no massive historical backfill required.

## 8. Known Issues & Potential Pitfalls

*   **API/HTML Changes at IdeaBrowser.com**\
    • Fix: build a robust scraper with selector fallback or request official API access.
*   **Rate Limits & Throttling**\
    • Fix: implement exponential backoff, caching, and error retries.
*   **Duplicate Idea Entries**\
    • Fix: ensure deduplication logic on title + source URL + date.
*   **Email Deliverability**\
    • Fix: use verified sending domain, monitor bounce rates, provide unsubscribe links.
*   **Real-Time Discussion Load**\
    • Fix: limit long polling or switch to WebSocket only for active threads; paginate comments.
*   **Time Zone Discrepancies**\
    • Fix: store all times in UTC; present based on user locale.

